      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Siding with UPSTAGE (9) who resumed at Kyneton and ran a credible race, no match for the winner but finding the line strongly for second with improvement to come. She's lightly raced and should relish getting to 1400m here, expect she takes plenty of holding out. SILKY SETH (7) was better last start at Ballarat when sticking on for third, out to 1500m there at Ballarat. He'll roll forward with Lane on and that could prove the difference. BRUTAL TEMPO (4) ran well on debut at Yarra Valley, running on well for a narrow third. Up in trip on a wider track here should suit nicely. TREBILCO (3) was just fair fresh at Pakenham but was right in the market there and could be a sharp improver. SIMPLY GOLD (8) resumes having shown some ability over further last time in, he can sprint well.",
